Sentencas: SrCe0.95Yb0.05O3 (SCY) and related materials are under consideration as a proton conductors for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) electrolytes.
Titulo: Influence of morphology on the behaviour of electrodes in a proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Sintered pellets of SCY are used to perforin impedance spectroscopy (IS) Studies and fuel cell tests on cells with Pt electrodes of two different morphologies.
Titulo: Influence of morphology on the behaviour of electrodes in a proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Electrodes are applied to the SCY pellets by two routes: either by firing on a layer of Pt paint (denoted electrode P) or by magnetron Sputtering (electrode S).
Titulo: Influence of morphology on the behaviour of electrodes in a proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: In impedance spectra recorded over a wide temperature range under humidified hydrogen, in symmetrical cell conditions, cells with S electrodes give rise to a Much smaller low frequency impedance feature than the cells with P electrodes.
Titulo: Influence of morphology on the behaviour of electrodes in a proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: This is tentatively attributed to faster diffusion-related processes taking place at the S electrodes.
Titulo: Influence of morphology on the behaviour of electrodes in a proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The behaviour of working fuel cells with S and P electrode morphologies is evaluated in terms of maximum power output and Area Specific Resistance in two-atmosphere tests.
Titulo: Influence of morphology on the behaviour of electrodes in a proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The fuel cell anode with the S morphology results in superior fuel cell performance, in agreement with the impedance study.
Titulo: Influence of morphology on the behaviour of electrodes in a proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The influence of the two different electrode morphologies oil the behaviour of the cells is discussed with reference to their morphology, as determined by SEM and AFM.
Titulo: Influence of morphology on the behaviour of electrodes in a proton-conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
